definition.value: A steroid aldehyde that is cortisol carrying a formyl group at position 18.
A p-menthane monoterpenoid that is p-menthane carrying a hydroxy group at position 1.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups positions 1 and 2 are specified as alpha-linolenoyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups positions 1 and 2 are specified as alpha-linolenoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups positions 1 and 2 are specified as alpha-linolenoyl and (11Z,14Z)-icosadienoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups positions 1 and 2 are specified as alpha-linolenoyl and (11Z)-icosenoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups positions 1 and 2 are specified as alpha-linolenoyl and icosanoyl (arachidoyl) respectively.
A monoterpene that is cyclohexa-1,3-diene substituted at positions 1 and 4 by methyl and prop-1-en-2-yl groups respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl and (11Z)-icosenoyl respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-icosatetraenoyl and arachidoyl (icosanoyl) respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (13Z,16Z)-docosadienoyl and linoleoyl respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (13Z,16Z)-docosadienoyl and hexadecanoyl respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as (10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatrienoyl and (9Z,12Z)-hexadecadienoyl respectively.
